{"id": 5999, "title": "Ticket #5999: GCE jobs should auto-delete their disk images", "description": "<blockquote>\nIn the current Google Compute Engine API, when you create an instance with a disk based on an image, the disk is left in place when the instance is deleted. This appears to be a change from earlier betas, where the default was to delete the disk as well.\n\n<p>The gce_gahp should explicitly request that the instance's disk be deleted when the instance is deleted.</p></blockquote>", "remarks": "<blockquote>\n<em>2016-Nov-09 13:55:19 by tlmiller:</em> <br/>\n\n<strong>Code Review</strong>\n\n<p>Ship it!</p></blockquote>", "derived_tickets": "", "attachments": "<html><head></head><body></body></html>", "check_ins": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2016-Nov-23 09:52</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/1cc57ac0583ca587eb11c9a1c16fc95284f8ceaa\">[49628]</a></span>: Docs for auto-delete or GCE disk imaages. <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=5999\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('5999'); return false;\" title=\"GCE jobs should auto-delete their disk images\">#5999</a></span>  (By Jaime Frey )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2016-Nov-08 14:44</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/eb111163ecd4c860b208cc588a837ec3bb6cb0ec\">[49562]</a></span>: GCE jobs should auto-delete their disk images. <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=5999\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('5999')